&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Remote – US (Open to applicants located in the USA)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fueled is a leading digital strategy, design, and engineering agency. Recently united with 10up – &lt;a href=&quot;https://10up.com/blog/2025/new-fueled-brand-10up-becomes-wordpress-practice/&quot;&gt;now the brand of our WordPress practice&lt;/a&gt; – we are a 300+ person team that has designed and built hundreds of digital products and experiences for brands like Google, Apple, The New York Times, ESPN, Victoria’s Secret, MGM Resorts, Albertsons, and CLEAR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;As a growing force in the digital services space, we’re building a brand that resonates, a growth engine that converts, and a team that scales impact. We&#39;re looking for a strategic and action-oriented &lt;strong&gt;VP, Marketing &amp;amp; Growth&lt;/strong&gt; to lead our full-funnel growth function from first impression to forming a long-term relationship.&amp;nbsp; This role is pivotal in strengthening our voice in the market, fueling demand, supporting conversion and enabling client retention and expansion.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Sitting at the intersection of marketing, brand, content, and revenue, this role partners cross-functionally with Product, Strategy, Client Services, and Executive Leadership to align messaging with motion, attention with action, and storytelling with sales. You’ll shape how we show up, what we say, and how we grow.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;With a sharp understanding of modern marketing infrastructure, a love for compelling narratives, and a metrics-driven mindset, you’ll help us grow our brand—and our business.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Elevate the Brand:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Define and evolve our brand positioning, voice, and visual identity. Champion our story in a way that resonates with ideal customers and amplifies market presence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Full-Funnel Marketing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Lead integrated strategies across paid, earned, and owned channels, brand campaigns, performance marketing, email, events, and more, to drive awareness, engagement, and conversion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Demand and Acquisition:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Launch always-on and campaign-based programs that attract, nurture, and convert the right audiences into pipeline and revenue.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Activate GTM Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Partner closely with business development and GTM teams to craft sequenced, personalized marketing plays that accelerate sales momentum and nurture prospects.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build Thought Leadership &amp;amp; Content:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Oversee the development of strategic content and enablement tools, from white papers to case studies that support both credibility and conversion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Refine ICP and Messaging:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Define and continuously evolve our Ideal Customer Profile (ICP), building segment-specific messaging that speaks to value and need.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Modernize Marketing Infrastructure:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Select and optimize tools for campaign execution, data enrichment, analytics, and personalization, bringing scale and precision to every motion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expand Ecosystem Influence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Cultivate relationships with analysts, partners, and collaborators who amplify our brand and enhance inbound quality.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Co-Own Pipeline and Revenue Targets:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Partner with sales leadership to track performance, optimize marketing contribution, and align on accountability for bottom-line impact.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and Inspire a High-Performing Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Guide a multidisciplinary team of marketers and business developers. Foster a culture of curiosity, experimentation, and results.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You bring 10+ years of marketing, business development, or growth leadership experience, ideally in digital agencies, consultancies, or productized services environments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You have a proven track record of building integrated marketing programs that generate brand awareness, demand, and qualified pipeline.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You think across the funnel, comfortable working in brand strategy one day and performance metrics the next. Content, campaign orchestration, and digital media are in your wheelhouse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re a collaborative operator who thrives in cross-functional environments. You’ve partnered closely with product, strategy, and client service teams to drive aligned growth outcomes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re fluent in modern marketing stacks and tools—including AI-enhanced platforms that support personalization, automation, targeting, and reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re a compelling communicator who understands how to craft a message, influence stakeholders, and rally a team around a shared vision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re detail-oriented, metrics-focused, and excited by the opportunity to scale fast with clarity and accountability.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &amp;amp; Salary&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Competitive salary and benefits. Compensation is determined based on a variety of factors including relevant experience, other job-related qualifications, geographic location, and business needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join our Team! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are passionate about Fueled&#39;s mission and think you have what it takes to be successful in this role, even if you don&#39;t check all the boxes - please apply. We&#39;d appreciate the opportunity to personally review your application. Everyone gets a response.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any data provided will be processed in accordance with applicable law and our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://fueled.com/privacy-policy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;privacy policy&lt;/a&gt;. Curious about what to expect during our talent process? Check it out&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/fueled/What-to-Expect-from-the-Interview-Process-at-Fueled-1d84dccd9d8b80f8a0b0d40b244f4caf?pvs=4&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fingerprint&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;empowers developers to stop online fraud at the source.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work on turning radical new ideas in the fraud detection space into reality. Our products are developer-focused and our clients range from solo developers to publicly traded companies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;We are a globally dispersed, 100% remote company&lt;/strong&gt; with a strong open-source focus. Our flagship open-source project is &lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/fingerprintjs/fingerprintjs&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://github.com/fingerprintjs/fingerprintjs&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;FingerprintJS&lt;/a&gt; (20K stars on GitHub).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/fingerprintjs&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/fingerprintjs&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;We have raised $77M&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;and are backed by Craft Ventures (previously invested in&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://www.tesla.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://www.tesla.com/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Tesla,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://facebook.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://facebook.com/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Facebook,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://www.airbnb.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://www.airbnb.com/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Airbnb&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;), Nexus Venture Partners (previously invested in &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.postman.com/&quot;&gt;Postman&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.apollo.io/&quot;&gt;Apollo.io,&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://min.io/&quot;&gt;MinIO&lt;/a&gt;, Druva)&amp;nbsp;and Uncorrelated Ventures (previously invested in&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://redis.io/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://redis.io/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Redis,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://rollbar.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://rollbar.com/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Rollbar&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://gradle.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://gradle.org/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Gradle&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We have noticed a rise in recruiting impersonations across the industry, where scammers attempt to access candidates&#39; personal and financial information through fake interviews and offers. All Fingerprint recruiting email communications will always come from the @fingerprint.com domain. Any outreach claiming to be from Fingerprint via other sources should be ignored.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;We are seeking a Senior IT Engineer to take ownership of our internal systems and infrastructure, drive automation, and lead the implementation of modern IT standards across the organization. This role is perfect for someone excited to scale secure, low-friction IT experiences in a fast-paced, remote-first environment. You&#39;ll work cross-functionally to ensure every team member has secure, reliable access to the tools they need from day one — while designing backend systems that are scalable, secure, and built for the long term.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Access &amp;amp; Automation:&lt;/strong&gt; Replace manual access requests with scalable, automated workflows. Implement SSO solutions and integrate provisioning into Rippling. Build IT ticketing systems and self-service portals to streamline support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure &amp;amp; Strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; Collaborate with leadership to define and drive IT roadmap, and create scalable processes for a growing remote team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Device Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Define desktop standards, manage MDM tools, and deploy zero-touch provisioning via Apple Business Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security:&lt;/strong&gt; Oversee endpoint protection, antivirus/EDR tools, OS and application patching, and secure data backup processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SaaS &amp;amp; Google Workspace:&lt;/strong&gt; Administer Google Workspace and manage tool integrations (Slack, Notion, GitHub, etc.) to ensure security and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Asset Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead full lifecycle hardware management — from procurement and onboarding to offboarding and decommissioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in IT engineering, infrastructure, or systems administration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience implementing Single Sign-On (SSO) solutions from start to finish.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong working knowledge of Google Workspace administration, SaaS management, and cloud-first infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in macOS device management, including MDM tools and Apple Business Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with zero-touch provisioning, endpoint security, and IT automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in replacing manual IT request systems with ticketing and workflow automation tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in scripting (e.g., Bash, Python) to support automation and infrastructure improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of GDPR and global data privacy/security practices and how to apply them in internal systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and documentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SOC 2, ISO 27001, or similar compliance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with zero trust architecture and principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in supporting distributed, remote-first teams across multiple time zones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt;The base salary range for this role is $180,000 - $205,000. For cash compensation, we set standard ranges for all US based roles based on function, level and geographic location, benchmarked against similar stage growth companies. In order to be compliant with local legislation, as well as to provide greater transparency to candidates, we share salary ranges on all job postings regardless of desired hiring location. Final offer amounts are determined by multiple factors including geographic location as well as candidate experience and expertise, and may vary from the amounts listed above.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We have noticed a rise in recruiting impersonations across the industry, where scammers attempt to access candidates&#39; personal and financial information through fake interviews and offers. All Fingerprint recruiting email communications will always come from the @fingerprint.com domain. Any outreach claiming to be from Fingerprint via other sources should be ignored.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Offers vary depending on, but not limited to, relevant experience, education, certifications/licenses, skills, training, and market conditions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to regulatory and security reasons, there’s a small number of countries where we cannot have Fingerprint teammates based.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Additionally, because Fingerprint is an all-remote company and people can join our workforce from almost any country, we do not sponsor visas. Fingerprint teammates need to be authorized to work from their home location&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are dedicated to creating an inclusive work environment for everyone. We embrace and celebrate the unique experiences, perspectives and cultural backgrounds that each employee brings to our workplace. Fingerprint strives to foster an environment where our employees feel respected, valued and empowered, and our team members are at the forefront in helping us promote and sustain an inclusive workplace. We highly encourage people from underrepresented groups in tech to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are applying as a resident of California, please read our CCPA notice &lt;a href=&quot;https://dev.fingerprint.com/docs/dpa-ccpa&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are applying as a resident of the EU, please read our GDPR notice &lt;a href=&quot;https://dev.fingerprint.com/docs/dpa-gdpr&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Canonical is a leading provider of open source software and operating systems to the global enterprise and technology markets. Our platform, Ubuntu, is very widely used in breakthrough enterprise initiatives such as public cloud, data science, AI, engineering innovation, and IoT. Our customers include the world&#39;s leading public cloud and silicon providers, and industry leaders in many sectors. The company is a pioneer of global distributed collaboration, with 1200+ colleagues in 75+ countries and very few office-based roles. Teams meet two to four times yearly in person, in interesting locations around the world, to align on strategy and execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The company is founder-led, profitable, and growing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Global System Integrators (GSI) play a crucial role in Canonical growth plans in the coming 3 years. We are hiring a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Partner Sales Director&lt;/strong&gt; to work closely with Canonical GSI partners throughout their sales cycles and across their sales organizations to facilitate Ubuntu based solutions and opportunities, as well as help GSI build long term digital transformation platforms with Ubuntu stacks and services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the VP Global Alliances and Channels, the Partner Sales Director&amp;nbsp;will be responsible for building trusted relationships with partners, increasing Canonical market share and attach rate, evangelizing about the partnership and leading all business interactions from engineers to CxO level. They will own the strategy, the sell-to, sell-through and sell-with motions with the GSI and will animate many customer workshops, sales events, public presentations and executive engagements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role entails&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strategic relationships with partners at levels, and stickiness with Ubuntu technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of Linux and cloud software ecosystem, and open source selling models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate contracts and commercial business terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of partner organizations and sales models, in particular with Global System Integrators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with marketing, sales engineering and product management to deliver on targets, objectives and provide a voice of the partner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead executive interlocks between partners and Canonical leadership team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel - sometimes internationally - up to 40% of the time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we are looking for in you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience in alliance or indirect sales management roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience with OpenStack, virtualization, containers and other Cloud technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Autonomous, disciplined, hands-on, get-it-done mentality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to capture customer requirements, evaluate gaps, identify and create opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about Ubuntu products and mission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable in fast-paced and high pressure environments with ambitious achievement goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer colleagues&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We consider geographical location, experience, and performance in shaping compensation worldwide. We revisit compensation annually (and more often for graduates and associates) to ensure we recognize outstanding performance. In addition to base pay, we offer a performance-driven annual bonus or commission. We provide all team members with additional benefits which reflect our values and ideals. We balance our programs to meet local needs and ensure fairness globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Distributed work environment with twice-yearly team sprints in person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal learning and development budget of USD 2,000 per year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual compensation review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recognition rewards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual holiday leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maternity and paternity leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team Member Assistance Program &amp;amp; Wellness Platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to travel to new locations to meet colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Priority Pass and travel upgrades for long-haul company events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Canonical&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Canonical is a pioneering tech firm at the forefront of the global move to open source. As the company that publishes Ubuntu, one of the most important open-source projects and the platform for AI, IoT, and the cloud, we are changing the world of software. We recruit on a global basis and set a very high standard for people joining the company. We expect excellence; in order to succeed, we need to be the best at what we do. Most colleagues at Canonical have worked from home since our inception in 2004.​ Working here is a step into the future and will challenge you to think differently, work smarter, learn new skills, and raise your game.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Canonical is an equal opportunity employer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to foster a workplace free from discrimination. Diversity of experience, perspectives, and background create a better work environment and better products.&lt;a href=&quot;https://canonical.com/careers/diversity/identity&quot;&gt; Whatever your identity, we will give your application fair consideration.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-remote&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Canonical is a leading provider of open source software and operating systems to the global enterprise and technology markets. Our platform, Ubuntu, is very widely used in breakthrough enterprise initiatives such as public cloud, data science, AI, engineering innovation and IoT. Our customers include the world&#39;s leading public cloud and silicon providers, and industry leaders in many sectors. The company is a pioneer of global distributed collaboration, with 1100+ colleagues in 75+ countries and very few office based roles. Teams meet two to four times yearly in person, in interesting locations around the world, to align on strategy and execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The company is founder led, profitable and growing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Partner Sales Manager to be a key contributing team member within the growing IHV alliances organization. Large OEM or Independent Hardware Vendor (IHV) brands - Dell, HPE, IBM, Lenovo, Ericsson, Cisco, Fujitsu and many more - are major partners for Canonical. These companies build software-defined solutions to capitalize on global open source mandates and associated macro trends. Canonical’s flagship product, Ubuntu, and its broader open source portfolio are key ingredients for these partners to realize their aspirations. Canonical represents the best platform for rapid open source innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Head of IHV Alliances, the Partner Sales Manager will work closely with IHV and Canonical teams in various geographies to enable IHV teams, generate and transact opportunities, drive a Canonical agenda within an IHV, and achieve targeted results. They are responsible to build trusted relationships with our partners, increase Canonical market share and attach rate, evangelize the partnership and drive business interactions from across persona - from engineer to CxO. They will often run customer workshops focused on particular initiatives at that customer, attend sales events, give public presentations and participate in executive engagements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: This is a remote role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The role entails&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strategic relationships and enable partner teams on the partnership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build pipeline and transact opportunities through an IHV&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow partner awareness of open source capabilities on Canonical Ubuntu&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a deep understanding of the Linux and cloud software ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver on targets, objectives and provide a voice of the partner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel regularly - sometimes internationally - to drive partnerships in person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align and support internal canonical field teams - identify, support, grow, transact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand existing footprint with IHV customers with an aim to upsell to broader portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
